<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Psammisia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Psammisia ramiflora" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ramiflora">Psammisia ramiflora</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Psammisia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Psammisia ramiflora" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ramiflora">Psammisia ramiflora</taxonomicName>
Klotzsch, Linnaea 24: 44 (1851). Type Protologue: In locis alpestribus Veraguae Americae centralis, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">de Warszewicz</emphasis>
. Type: [label 1] Costa Rica et Veragua Chiriqui, [label 2] Zentral America, de Warszewicz s.n. (holotype, B destroyed, photograph at F! negative no. 4698, https://fm-digital-assets.fieldmuseum.org/26/134/4698.jpg; lectotype, labeled by Leutyn in 2006 and designated here, Costa Rica and Veragua, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Warszewicz s.n.</emphasis>
G 352123!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Psammisia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Psammisia" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Psammisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a Neotropic genus of terrestrial or epiphytic shrubs from the 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Psammisia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Ericaceae</taxonomicName>
family, consisting of ca. 50 species. Its distribution ranges from Costa Rica southward into Bolivia and eastward to French Guiana and Trinidad (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/2395354" author="Wilbur, RL" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="27 - 143" refId="B53" refString="Wilbur, RL, Luteyn, JL, 1978. Flora of Panama. Part VIII. Family 149. Ericaceae. Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 65 (1): 27 - 143, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/2395354" title="Flora of Panama. Part VIII. Family 149. Ericaceae." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/2395354" volume="65" year="1978">Wilbur and Luteyn 1978</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="The Plant List" journalOrPublisher="PhytoKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" publicationUrl="http://www.theplantlist.org/" refId="B46" refString="The Plant List, 2021. Version 1.1. 2013. http://www.theplantlist.org/" title="Version 1.1. 2013." url="http://www.theplantlist.org/" year="2021">The Plant List 2021</bibRefCitation>
). Within the genus, one of the most variable morphologically is 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Psammisia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Psammisia ramiflora" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ramiflora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Psammisia ramiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, known only from Costa Rica and Panama. The taxon was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Klotzsch, JF" journalOrPublisher="Linnaea" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 88" refId="B24" refString="Klotzsch, JF, 1851. Studien ueber die natuerliche Klasse Bicornes Linne. Linnaea 24: 1 - 88" title="Studien ueber die natuerliche Klasse Bicornes Linne." volume="24" year="1851">Klotzsch (1851)</bibRefCitation>
based on 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Warszewiczâ€™s">Warszewicz's</normalizedToken>
gathering, destroyed during the war. During our studies, we found only one specimen collected by Warszewicz and determined by Klotzsch as 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. ramiflora" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="ramiflora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">P. ramiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The specimen is preserved in G herbarium. However, its label slightly differs from both, specified in the protologue and on the type specimen photographed by Macbride (F negative no. 4698). Nevertheless, it constitutes a duplicate of the holotype. In 2006, Luteyn labelled this specimen as the lectotype of the species; however, he did not designate it in publication. Thus, we here propose to designate the specimen preserved in G (https://www.ville-ge.ch/musinfo/bd/cjb/chg/adetail.php?id=238797&amp;base=img&amp;lang=en) as the lectotype of 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. ramiflora" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="ramiflora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">P. ramiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
